Good copy and a good movie. The scope of the movie is restricted to the chain of events before and during the crash and is reasonably factual and informative. The owner's clique behind the financial system and their ideology is not tackled but that's kind of hard to do anyway without entering conspiracy territory. The movie does not tell the whole story, including how the system is intentionally set up to move real wealth from the middle class to the banksters - but the omission does not seem to be 'malicious' in any way. The last part that deals with the corruption of the economist profession is very interesting. That issue needs to receive more attention. On the whole a good and informative movie and a must see for those who want to know who stole the world's wealth, how they did it and how they are still doing it. I'll be seeding it for a long time.
